      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely valid to feel that logical when the world feels too unstable to keep, and your frustration with \"positive thinking\" is a healthy response to a broken reality. However, trying to stay fully engaged in a sinking ship can be dangerous, so it might actually be wiser to step back from the news and protect your own mental space rather than forcing yourself to care. Building a life doesn't mean ignoring the bigger problems, but it does mean choosing where to focus your limited energy so you don't get consumed by the chaos. If the weight of this \"logical\" conclusion feels paralyzing, please reach out to a therapist or support group who can help you navigate these deep feelings of hopelessness without judgment.",
